# Main.elm — EARLY

Thin port-owning harness around `Main.Play`. Wires
`Browser.element` with Play's init/update/view/subscriptions;
owns the URL-pinning port (only port modules may declare
ports); wraps Play's embeddable view in a viewport-filling
shell so the main app looks full-screen.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Slim by design after
  REFACTOR_EMBEDDABLE_PLAY (2026-04-23). Below ~70 lines and
  should stay that way — if Main.elm starts growing, the
  weight probably belongs inside Play or further down the
  stack.

## Responsibilities

Everything here is host-level:

- `port setSessionPath : String -> Cmd msg` — updates the URL
  path to `/gopher/lynrummy-elm/play/<sid>` when Play emits
  `SessionChanged`. Reloads resume the same session via
  server-rendered `initialSessionId` in the page flags.
- `Browser.element` boot.
- `configFromFlags` — maps `Flags` (from HTML) to a
  `Play.Config`:
  - `initialSessionId == Just sid` → `ResumeSession sid`
  - `Nothing` → `NewSession`
- Viewport-filling outer div — fixed-to-viewport, scroll,
  background — wrapping `Play.view`. BOARD_LAB skips this
  wrapper; puzzle panels scroll normally in the gallery.
- Routing `Play.Output` through the port. `NoOutput` is a
  plain `(model, cmd)` pass-through.

## What NOT to put here

Anything that pertains to gameplay, session bootstrap, drag,
replay, or rendering. That all lives in `Main.Play` (and its
submodules). Main.elm should remain a harness you can replace
with a different host (e.g., Lab.elm) without losing
functionality.

## Pointers

- `Main.Play` — the embeddable component (everything the
  main app actually does).
- `games/lynrummy/board-lab/elm/src/Lab.elm` — the lab's
  host; shows that Main.Play is embeddable.
